data.title: Manchester United coaching staff members isolating ahead of Newcastle game, Solskjaer unaffected
data.meta_description: Nicky Butt and Mark Dempsey will be on Manchester United’s bench in tonight’s Premier League game with Newcastle after several forced to isolate.
data.text:
ByRichard Newman

Updated 21/02/2021 at 13:30 GMT

Nicky Butt and Mark Dempsey will join Manchester United manager Ole Gunnar Solskjaer on the bench for Sunday night’s Premier League game with Newcastle after several other, unnamed, members of the coaching staff were forced to isolate. It is understood no players are affected.

Manchester United manager Ole Gunnar Solskjaer and Nicky Butt

Image credit: Getty Images

Manchester United will be without several of their usual touchline staff for tonight’s Premier League game with Newcastle, after a number were forced to isolate.

Nicky Butt and Mark Dempsey, who work with the youth players, will step up to provide support for manager Ole Gunnar Solskjaer on the bench.

United have not revealed who the individuals are, or whether they have tested positive for coronavirus, but it is understood no players are affected.

Butt, who is currently the club’s head of development, is a former team-mate of Solskjaer’s, while Dempsey, who once played for United, was a previous assistant of the Norwegian’s at Molde and Cardiff City.

United will be attempting to end a run of two Premier League draws when they take on struggling Newcastle at Old Trafford at 7pm.
